OL,6,FThis bizarre scheduling decision has
OL,7,Fhappened before with The Apprentice
OL,8,Ffinal but sends out all the wrong
OL,9,Fsignals.
OL,11,FWe have discussed before how it is
OL,12,Fdifficult for BBC One to run post-
OL,13,Fwatershed programmes ` for instance
OL,14,Fpowerful single dramas ` which are
OL,15,Fmore than 60 minutes long.
OL,17,FThis is why it is acceptable to move
OL,18,Fback the news, for example, on a
OL,19,FSunday or holiday to allow
OL,20,Fexceptional output. At Christmas I
OL,21,Fjustified the decision to delay the
OL,22,Fnews for the harrowing war film 1917.
OL,3,CLet's not make a habit of moving BBC
OL,4,COne news programmes
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
